-- Turkey's Akbank signs deal with EIB on bond issue worth 425 mln lira 
-- By Humeyra Pamuk
-- Wed Dec 24, 2014 03:13AM EST
-- None



ISTANBUL, Dec 24 (Reuters) - Turkish lender Akbank <AKBNK.IS> said on Wednesday it haD signed a deal with the European Investment Bank (EIB) for the issue of mortgage-covered bonds worth 425 million lira ($183.5 million) and with a five-year maturity.

